  "responseElements": "<p>If the action is successful, the service sends back an HTTP 200 response.</p><p>The following data is returned in JSON format by the service.</p><div class=\"variablelist\">\n          \n          \n          \n      <dl>\n            <dt id=\"bedrock-agent-runtime_Retrieve-response-guardrailAction\"><span class=\"term\">\n               <b>\n                  <a href=\"#API_agent-runtime_Retrieve_ResponseSyntax\">guardrailAction</a>\n               </b>\n            </span></dt>\n            <dd>\n               <p>Specifies if there is a guardrail intervention in the response.</p>\n               <p>Type: String</p>\n               <p>Valid Values: <code class=\"code\">INTERVENED | NONE</code>\n               </p>\n            </dd>\n          \n            <dt id=\"bedrock-agent-runtime_Retrieve-response-nextToken\"><span class=\"term\">\n               <b>\n                  <a href=\"#API_agent-runtime_Retrieve_ResponseSyntax\">nextToken</a>\n               </b>\n            </span></dt>\n            <dd>\n               <p>If there are more results than can fit in the response, the response returns a <code class=\"code\">nextToken</code>. Use this token in the <code class=\"code\">nextToken</code> field of another request to retrieve the next batch of results.</p>\n               <p>Type: String</p>\n               <p>Length Constraints: Minimum length of 1. Maximum length of 2048.</p>\n               <p>Pattern: <code class=\"code\">^\\S*$</code>\n               </p>\n            </dd>\n          \n            <dt id=\"bedrock-agent-runtime_Retrieve-response-retrievalResults\"><span class=\"term\">\n               <b>\n                  <a href=\"#API_agent-runtime_Retrieve_ResponseSyntax\">retrievalResults</a>\n               </b>\n            </span></dt>\n            <dd>\n               <p>A list of results from querying the knowledge base.</p>\n               <p>Type: Array of <a href=\"./API_agent-runtime_KnowledgeBaseRetrieval